+Line and branch coverage measure the lines existing scenarios execute, not whether every behaviour a seam supports is asserted: a 100%-covered seam still owes a `@captain` gap for each boundary or error behaviour no scenario names. The ledger is what makes that visible, so a seam absent from it, or present with only a coverage number, is an incomplete report rather than a clean one.
